1.can be in either on of the formats:
a) function funcName{
	<commands>
}

b) funcName(){
	<commands>
}

2. The function declration MUST be BEFORE any call to it within the script (similar to C/C++).

3. It can read its argument the same way a script recvies its command line argument,via $1,$2,etc...

4. Variables within functions can and should be declared local.


